race.comment: Plenty of chances. LITTLE LUNCH (8) is Sydney-trained and well placed off a 1.4L defeat at Hawkesbury over 1800m. She will have taken fitness from that and this is winnable with average luck. ANULFA (3) presents third-up off decent efforts here. Stepped up to this trip in better grade last time and didn't have the best of it at the business end. She should be right in it. The Seib yard is flying, and ZIGGY ROSE (6) will have admirers stepping up to the middle distance. Made ground after a slow start at Goulburn over a mile and arrives here at peak fitness. DUNWITHYA (1) found one much too good at Goulburn but covered the others. Ran a number that puts him right in this, and he'll present at peak fitness.
